cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentence ranking and fact-checking. It may also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves gathering related information to sentences. Additionally, the use of neural networks for ranking and weak supervision for training suggests that it may belong to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of syntactic dependencies in sentences may also suggest a potential fit for the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
